{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3501"},"text":"§ 3501.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional statement of findings and purpose","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress finds that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" coastal barriers along the Atlantic and Gulf coasts and along the shore areas of the Great Lakes of the United States and the adjacent wetlands, marshes, estuaries, inlets and nearshore waters provide—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" habitats for migratory birds and other wildlife; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" habitats which are essential spawning, nursery, nesting, and feeding areas for commercially and recreationally important species of finfish and shellfish, as well as other aquatic organisms such as sea turtles;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d84f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" coastal barriers contain resources of extraordinary scenic, scientific, recreational, natural, historic, archeological, cultural, and economic importance; which are being irretrievably damaged and lost due to development on, among, and adjacent to, such barriers;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d850-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" coastal barriers serve as natural storm protective buffers and are generally unsuitable for development because they are vulnerable to hurricane and other storm damage and because natural shoreline recession and the movement of unstable sediments undermine manmade structures;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d851-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" certain actions and programs of the Federal Government have subsidized and permitted development on coastal barriers and the result has been the loss of barrier resources, threats to human life, health, and property, and the expenditure of millions of tax dollars each year; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d852-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a program of coordinated action by Federal, State, and local governments is critical to the more appropriate use and conservation of coastal barriers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d853-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3501/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress declares that it is the purpose of this chapter to minimize the loss of human life, wasteful expenditure of Federal revenues, and the damage to fish, wildlife, and other natural resources associated with the coastal barriers along the Atlantic and Gulf coasts and along the shore areas of the Great Lakes by restricting future Federal expenditures and financial assistance which have the effect of encouraging development of coastal barriers, by establishing the John H. Chafee Coastal Barrier Resources System, and by considering the means and measures by which the long-term conservation of these fish, wildlife, and other natural resources may be achieved.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id79b9d854-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/348/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–348, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1653"},"text":"96 Stat. 1653","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/707/tII/s204/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–707, title II, § 204(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-23"},"text":"Nov. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4714"},"text":"102 Stat. 4714","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/167/s3/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–167, § 3(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-12-09"},"text":"Dec. 9, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1804"},"text":"113 Stat. 1804","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id79b9d855-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id79b9d856-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id79b9d857-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/348"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–348","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1653"},"text":"96 Stat. 1653","children":[],"tail":", known as the Coastal Barrier Resources Act, which is classified generally to this chapter (§ 3501 et seq.). For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out below and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id79b9d858-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–167","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the John H. Chafee Coastal Barrier Resources System” for “a Coastal Barrier Resources System”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsecs. (a)(1), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/707"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–707","children":[],"tail":" inserted “and along the shore areas of the Great Lakes” after “Atlantic and Gulf coasts”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id79b9d859-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id79b9d85a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2024 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/117/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–117, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1608"},"text":"138 Stat. 1608","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/117/s1"},"text":"“This Act [amending sections 3502 to 3506 and 3510 of this title and enacting provisions set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s3504"},"text":"section 3504 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and listed in a table of Revision of Maps for Units of System set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s3503"},"text":"section 3503 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Bolstering Ecosystems Against Coastal Harm Act’ or the ‘BEACH Act’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id79b9d85b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"tex